{
  "texts": [
    "Co-updating LLM and LoRAThe above two kinds of methods focus on improving the representation ability of LoRA itself.",
    "Different from them, Delta-LoRA [27] proposes to jointly update the LLM and LoRA modules, which directly updates the high-rank LLM and can gain better representation capable than updating LoRA independently.",
    "It updates the LLM based on the difference between two LoRA modules of two consecutive iterations, which enables it to update the LLM without any extra memory.",
    "Dynamic rank allocationFor the rank of LoRA, higher is not always better.",
    "The abundant LoRA ranks may cause degeneration in both performance and efficiency."
  ]
}